Police are conducting a raid in Kliptown, Soweto. They are clamping down on criminal activity in the area following multiple deaths in recent days. The township has been experiencing a series of gang-related violence. Three people were killed last week, allegedly by members of a gang called DSS. Fed up residents then took matters into their hands and necklaced one of the alleged perpetrators, shortly after he was released from police custody. Click on the videos below:  